2025.title: NASA Draws Closer to Artemis II
2025.description: NASA integrated the Artemis II Orion stage adapter with the rest of the SLS (Space Launch System) rocket on Wednesday in the Vehicle Assembly Building at the agency’s  Kennedy Space Center in Florida.

2025.title: Astrobee Robotics Platform Goes Commercial
2025.description: NASA’s free-flying Astrobee robot aboard the ISS is transitioning into commercial operations through Arkisys Inc. The move will expand private-sector access to zero-gravity robotics research, with new experiments in space autonomy and docking systems

2025.title: SpaceX launched its 10,000th satellite to orbit
2025.description: SpaceX has lofted 9,988 Starlink satellites to date, according to astrophysicist and satellite tracker Jonathan McDowell. So today's launch will take that number above 10,000. It will also be the record-breaking 31st liftoff for this Falcon 9's first stage.
